verbose_text: In their animal model study, Yang et al. [XREF_BIBR] examined the influence of changeable oestradiol doses (10 and 50 mug / rat per day for 11 consecutive days) on the behaviour of the animals and on the expression of tryptophan hydroxylase (TPH) and glucocorticoid receptor in the raphe nucleus of ovariectomised rats that were undergoing a forced swim test.
evidence: expression of tryptophan hydroxylase (TPH) and glucocorticoid receptor
